Name: Albana
Characteristics: summer and autumn leek, 20-22cm white stem, high yield.

Name: Cisco (Pancho)
Characteristics: early maturing; produces leeks with 12 to 16 inch shafts; plants medium green, upright, easy to peel, vigorous; bolting tolerant.

Name: Gabilan (325.012)
Characteristics: open pollinated, shaft very long and white; no bulbing; leaves are dark green and upstanding; fast growing.

Name: Kamush
Characteristics: harvest period September to October, very long white-green stems, stem length approximately 50 cm. 1991.

Name: Porino
Characteristics: late autumn and winter cropping, high frost resistance, very dark green leaves, 18-20 cm white stem.

Name: Quickstar
Characteristics: very uniform green type with strong leaf growth, easy to harvest.

Name: Rami (NUN 4011)
Characteristics: summer leek, very early, 20-24 cm white stem.

Name: Romil (NUN 6015)
Characteristics: suitable for autumn cropping, 22-24 cm white stem. 1989.

Name: Vriza (NUN 9005)
Characteristics: for winter and late winter harvest, dark green foliage. 1993.

Name: Wesa (NUN 8003)
Characteristics: dark blue erect foliage, shaft length 18 cm, autumn and winter type. 1993.
